*.duckdb
# ...but the committed self-index IS tracked: it is a real `orbit index` of THIS
# repo that the static build + CI drift check require (CI has no orbit binary to
# regenerate it). It is read-only graph data, no secrets. See scripts/build_static.py.
!data/keystone_self_graph.duckdb
# ...and the hero Orbit index of pallets/click IS tracked too: the headline number
# (Parameter x HelpFormatter, 64 shared dependents) must reproduce on a committed
# artifact, so a fresh clone can run find_top_collision and get the same count.
# test_hero_cache_click_reproduces_from_committed_orbit_graph asserts it. No secrets.
!data/click_graph.duckdb
# ...and the two secondary hero graphs, so EVERY cited collision number reproduces on a
# committed artifact: six (_resolve x __get_module, 3) and requests (values x set_cookie, 48).
# Built by scripts/build_external_graphs.py; pinned by tests/test_external_repo.py. No secrets.
!data/six_graph.duckdb
!data/requests_graph.duckdb
# ...and two real JS/TS libraries (tree-sitter-parsed), so the SAME engine is proven on JS AND TS
# end-to-end, not only Python: axios (JS, isObject x isBuffer, 24) and zod (TS, clone x mergeDefs,
# 39). Built by scripts/build_external_graphs.py; pinned by tests. No secrets.
!data/axios_graph.duckdb
!data/zod_graph.duckdb
# ...and the synthetic Orbit Remote SDLC fixture (real gl_codeowners/gl_commit_recency/
# gl_pipeline_history/gl_security_finding schema, synthetic data) that powers the ownership-entropy
# / pipeline-health / dependency-quarantine gates. Built by scripts/build_orbit_remote_fixture.py.
!data/orbit_remote_fixture.duckdb
schema_snapshot.local.json

